## 18. Glossary

---

### Purpose

The glossary defines key terms used throughout this specification to ensure clarity and consistency.

---

### Terms

**Active Pass** â€” A currently open pass in the Active Passes sheet.

**Admin** â€” A user with full privileges, including Settings edits and Emergency Mode control.

**Admin Panel** â€” The Admin UI that displays all passes and provides full override capabilities.

**Autonomy Trigger** â€” Teacher/support-controlled setting for allowing or restricting pass creation to/from locations.

**Cache** â€” Temporary storage of sheet data to optimize performance.

**DestinationID** (DEST ID) â€” The label representing a pass destination.

**Dev** â€” Developer with full access to code, migration, and system health functions.

**Emergency Mode** â€” Special mode where Admins trigger system-wide behavior changes.

**Emergency Panel** â€” The special UI shown to all staff during Emergency Mode.

**Emergency Log** â€” Canonical record of Emergency Mode actions and check-ins.

**Found Without Pass** â€” A flagged event when a student is observed in hallway without valid pass.

**IN Scheduled Class** â€” The default system assumption when no pass is active.

**Leg ID** â€” Counter incremented each time a pass changes state.

**Long Duration (LD)** â€” Flag for passes exceeding the configured long duration threshold.

**Override** â€” When a higher authority (Admin/support/teacher) force-closes or replaces an active pass.

**Pass ID** â€” The unique identifier for a pass.

**Pass Log** â€” Canonical audit sheet for all pass state changes.

**Permanent Record** â€” Long-term archive of closed passes.

**Scheduled Pass** â€” A future-scheduled pass entered by Admin/support/teacher.

**Staff ID** â€” Unique identifier for staff (teachers, support, admin).

**Student ID** â€” Unique identifier for students.

**Student UI** â€” The mobile-first student-facing pass interface.

**Teacher UI** â€” The teacher-facing UI for writing and managing passes.

**UI** â€” User interface, the interactive screens seen by users (students, staff, admin).

**Emergency Override** â€” Admin-level or system-level action that bypasses normal flow during an emergency.

**Found Without Pass Log** â€” Record tracking students located in hallway without a valid pass.

**Responsibility** â€” The current staff member/location responsible for a student.

**Scheduled Class** â€” The class where the student is expected to be during the current period.

**Student Autonomy** â€” The design principle allowing students to manage their own pass state within controlled boundaries.

**Teacher Autonomy** â€” The design principle allowing teachers to opt in or restrict student-initiated passes to/from their locations.

**Hierarchy of Authority** â€” The established precedence order for override actions: Admin > Support > Teacher > Student.

**System Settings** â€” Configurable parameters controlling system-wide behavior.

**Audit Trail** â€” Permanent record of key system events and changes for transparency and accountability.

**Version Tag** â€” Identifier marking versions of system code/spec.

**SIS Integration** â€” Future linkage with Student Information System (such as Infinite Campus) to automate data.

**Floating Teacher** â€” A teacher assigned to multiple rooms rather than a single fixed location.

**Hallway State** â€” The OUT state when a student is actively moving and not checked into a destination.

**Restroom Special Case** â€” The pass case where restroom acts as a temporary destination but does not require check-in.

**Emergency Check-In** â€” The act of a teacher/staff member claiming responsibility for a student during Emergency Mode.

**Emergency Activation** â€” The event when an admin turns Emergency Mode ON.

**Emergency Deactivation** â€” The event when an admin turns Emergency Mode OFF.

**Period Override** â€” Flag allowing specific locations to operate outside normal period schedule restrictions.

**UI Disable** â€” UI behavior where certain buttons are disabled to prevent invalid actions.

**Conflict Notification** â€” A system alert to users when actions conflict with scheduled passes or hierarchy rules.

**Orphaned Pass** â€” A pass with inconsistent or incomplete state (example: no matching student).

**Audit Safe** â€” A principle ensuring all state changes are logged without silent overrides.

